Project Report: Digital Literacy Infographic
For this task, I designed a Digital Literacy Awareness Infographic using Canva. I chose this tool because its drag-and-drop interface allowed me to blend a professional, educational layout with engaging visual elements that make complex information more accessible.
My design is divided into three core pillars: defining digital literacy, highlighting essential tools like Google Docs and Notion, and outlining safe internet practices. Visually, I utilized a textured paper background to give the digital content a tactile, grounded feel. I strategically placed a 3D-style illustration in the center to bridge the gap between the text columns, ensuring the viewer's eye flows naturally from the definition of digital literacy toward practical safety tips.
One thing I found particularly interesting during the design process was visual hierarchy. I learned how small adjustments in font weight and underlining could significantly impact how quickly a reader absorbs information. The most difficult part was balancing the "Negative Space"—ensuring that the infographic didn't feel cluttered while still including all the necessary bullet points for students to stay safe and productive online
